{"body": "I'm a fan of simple, established names when available. I call those things integration tests or system tests, and I don't really distinguish between those two types any more. Calling them \"request\" or \"resource\" tests doesn't afford communication with other people. If you talk to a J2EE or Django programmer about your resource tests you're going to get a blank stare. ;)", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/9279250", "created_at": "2012-10-09T20:49:12Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7878#issuecomment-9279250", "updated_at": "2012-10-09T20:49:12Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7878, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garybernhardt/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garybernhardt/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garybernhardt/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/garybernhardt", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garybernhardt/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/garybernhardt", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garybernhardt/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/0f3aad429c4fe35ea2bcffa654995a5e?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F8bfcbdd65996c417acdfad207838abb9.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garybernhardt/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garybernhardt/received_events", "gravatar_id": "0f3aad429c4fe35ea2bcffa654995a5e", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garybernhardt/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "garybernhardt", "type": "User", "id": 45707, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garybernhardt/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237f7febd3543c15100b19d"}, "id": 9279250, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7878"}
